---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'Framer vs Durable: Which AI Website Builder is Better?',
  description: 'Framer is easier and faster for landing pages. Durable is better for service businesses with AI-generated content. Framer $16+/mo, Durable $15+/mo. Side-by-side comparison.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['Framer vs Durable', 'AI website builder comparison', 'Framer review', 'Durable review', 'best AI website builder'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-[#0099FF]/5 to-[#E07A5F]/5 py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#0099FF] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        AI Tool Comparison · 2025 Updated
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        Framer vs Durable
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        Framer and Durable are both AI-powered website builders but they target different users. Framer is better for designers, marketing pages, and portfolios. Durable is better for service businesses who need complete websites with AI-generated content. Framer is faster and easier. Durable generates more comprehensive sites.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white bg-opacity-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick answer: Choose Framer if you want beautiful landing pages quickly and you care about design. Choose Durable if you're a service business (plumber, consultant, agency) who needs a complete website with all pages and AI-written content. Framer is $16+/month. Durable is $15+/month. Similar pricing, different strengths.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- At a Glance -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Framer vs Durable At a Glance
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold"></th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Framer</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Durable</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Best for</td>
            <td class="p-4">Designers, portfolios, landing pages</td>
            <td class="p-4">Service businesses, complete websites</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">AI features</td>
            <td class="p-4">Design assistance, content suggestions</td>
            <td class="p-4">Full website generation with content</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Ease of use</td>
            <td class="p-4">Very easy (drag-and-drop)</td>
            <td class="p-4">Very easy (AI generates everything)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Design quality</td>
            <td class="p-4">Excellent (modern, beautiful)</td>
            <td class="p-4">Good (functional, less polished)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Starting price</td>
            <td class="p-4">$16/month (Pro)</td>
            <td class="p-4">$15/month (Starter)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">CMS</td>
            <td class="p-4">Yes (built-in)</td>
            <td class="p-4">No (static mostly)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Ecommerce</td>
            <td class="p-4">Yes (via Stripe)</td>
            <td class="p-4">No (basic booking only)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Framer Overview -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Framer Does Best
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">1. Design-Focused</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Framer excels at visual design:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Beautiful templates:</strong> Modern, trendy designs</li>
          <li>• <strong>Animation tools:</strong> Smooth micro-interactions</li>
          <li>• <strong>Typography:</strong> Excellent font handling</li>
          <li>• <strong>Responsive:</strong> Mobile looks great automatically</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Portfolios, landing pages, marketing sites where design matters.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">2. Speed and Ease</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Framer is incredibly fast:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Template-based:</strong> Start with template, customize</li>
          <li>• <strong>Drag-and-drop:</strong> Intuitive visual editing</li>
          <li>• <strong>Real-time preview:</strong> See changes instantly</li>
          <li>• <strong>Fast to publish:</strong> Click to go live</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> People who want beautiful sites quickly without coding.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">3. CMS and Blogging</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Framer has built-in CMS:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Content management:</strong> Built-in blog CMS</li>
          <li>• <strong>Dynamic pages:</strong> Generate pages from content</li>
          <li>• <strong>Easy blogging:</strong> Write posts like docs</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Content creators who need blog or content management.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Durable Overview -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Durable Does Best
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">1. Complete Website Generation</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Durable generates full websites:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Multiple pages:</strong> Home, services, about, contact</li>
          <li>• <strong>AI-written content:</strong> Professional copy for your business</li>
          <li>• <strong>Service-specific:</strong> Knows what plumbers/consultants need</li>
          <li>• <strong>30 seconds:</strong> Entire site generated in under a minute</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Service businesses who need complete sites with content fast.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">2. Business Features</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Durable includes business tools:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>CRM:</strong> Built-in customer management</li>
          <li>• <strong>Invoicing:</strong> Create and send invoices</li>
          <li>• <strong>AI assistant:</strong> AI helper for business tasks</li>
          <li>• <strong>Analytics:</strong> Website traffic insights</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Small businesses who want all-in-one solution.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">3. AI-First Approach</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Durable is built around AI:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Everything is AI:</strong> Content, design, suggestions</li>
          <li>• <strong>Conversational:</strong> Tell AI what you need</li>
          <li>• <strong>Iterative:</strong> Ask AI to refine, add, change</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Non-technical users who want AI to do the work.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Use Cases -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      When to Choose Each
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Choose Framer if:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• You care about design quality (aesthetics matter)</li>
          <li>• You're building portfolio or marketing site</li>
          <li>• You need CMS or blogging</li>
          <li>• You want ecommerce (Stripe integration)</li>
          <li>• You're comfortable with drag-and-drop editing</li>
          <li>• You want highly customizable design</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Choose Durable if:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• You're service business (plumber, consultant, agency)</li>
          <li>• You need complete website fast (all pages, content)</li>
          <li>• You want AI-written content (saves time)</li>
          <li>• You need CRM/invoicing built-in</li>
          <li>• You're non-technical and want AI to do everything</li>
          <li>• You don't care about cutting-edge design trends</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Feature Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Feature Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Feature</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Framer</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Durable</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">AI generation</td>
            <td class="p-4">Partial (design help)</td>
            <td class="p-4">Full (site + content)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Templates</td>
            <td class="p-4">Many (beautiful)</td>
            <td class="p-4">Fewer (functional)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">CMS</td>
            <td class="p-4">Yes (built-in)</td>
            <td class="p-4">No (static)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Ecommerce</td>
            <td class="p-4">Yes (Stripe)</td>
            <td class="p-4">No (booking only)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">CRM</td>
            <td class="p-4">No (integration needed)</td>
            <td class="p-4">Yes (built-in)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Invoicing</td>
            <td class="p-4">No</td>
            <td class="p-4">Yes</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Blog</td>
            <td class="p-4">Yes</td>
            <td class="p-4">No</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Custom domains</td>
            <td class="p-4">Yes (Pro+)</td>
            <td class="p-4">Yes (paid plans)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Free trial</td>
            <td class="p-14">Yes (14 days)</td>
            <td class="p-14">Yes (available)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Starting price</td>
            <td class="p-14">$16/month</td>
            <td class="p-14">$15/month</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom Line -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="bg-white bg-opacity-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-6">Bottom Line</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Framer and Durable serve different needs. Neither is universally "better."</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6"><strong>Choose Framer if you want:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• Beautiful design that wows visitors</li>
        <li>• Portfolio, marketing site, or landing page</li>
        <li>• Blog or CMS for content</li>
        <li>• Ecommerce to sell products</li>
        <li>• Highly customizable design system</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6"><strong>Choose Durable if you want:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• Complete website with all pages (home, services, about, contact)</li>
        <li>• AI-written content for your business</li>
        <li>• CRM and invoicing built-in</li>
        <li>• Fast setup for service businesses</li>
        <li>• All-in-one business solution</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700"><strong>Can't go wrong either way:</strong> Both have free trials. Try both. See which interface you prefer. Both are solid AI website builders.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Related Comparisons
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/framer-vs-webflow" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Framer vs Webflow</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">No-code builders compared</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/webflow-vs-wordpress" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Webflow vs WordPress</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Platform comparison</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
